House Resolution 567
By: Representatives Cannon of the 172nd and Ford of the 170th
A RESOLUTION
1 Honoring the life of Mr. Zera D. Storey and dedicating an interchange in his memory; and
2 for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, Mr. Zera D. Storey has long been recognized by the citizens of this state for the
4 vital role that he has played in leadership and his deep personal commitment to the welfare
5 of the citizens of Georgia; and
6 WHEREAS, Mr. Storey was born on December 6, 1904, in Brooks County, Georgia, the
7 eldest son of David Storey and Letha Touchton, and he moved to Cook County, Georgia, in
8 1920; and
9 WHEREAS, Mr. Storey was raised in a sharecropper's house by his parents, growing up with
10 very little schooling and working as a farmer and business entrepreneur until his retirement;
11 and
12 WHEREAS, he was respected and admired by the people of Cook County, Georgia, sharing
13 labor with local farmers and becoming well known for his willingness to meet the needs of
14 others; and
