15 WHEREAS, Mr. Storey's life of strength, courage, service, and perseverance serves as an
16 inspiration to all Georgians, and he will be remembered as a man of great faith, humor, and
17 warmth, always quick to champion what was right and to speak out against what was wrong,
18 his solid integrity was a moral strength to all who knew him; and
19 WHEREAS, he was a devoted member of the Church of Christ in Adel, Georgia, where he
20 gave of his time, talents, gifts, and prayers; taught Bible classes for over 40 years; was an
21 active song leader; and participated in many gospel singing events and graveside memorials;
22 and
23 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that this remarkable and distinguished
24 Georgian be recognized appropriately by dedicating an interchange in his memory.
25 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED AND ENACTED BY THE GENERAL
26 ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA that the interchange of Interstate 75 and Springhill Road in
27 Cook County is dedicated as the Zera D. Storey Memorial Interchange.
28 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Department of Transportation is authorized and
29 directed to erect and maintain appropriate signs dedicating the Zera D. Storey Memorial
30 Interchange.
31 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
32 and directed to make appropriate copies of this resolution available for distribution to the
33 family of Mr. Zera D. Storey and the Department of Transportation.
